					<head>Pentateuch</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
						<summary>Pentateuch with Hafṭarot and the Five Scrolls.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" n="0">
							<locus from="1r" to="297v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Torah, hafṭarot u-megilot </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תורה, הפטרות ומגילות</title>
							<note>
								<p>This is the first of two uniform volumes, the second being Ms Add 9402 <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">70</ref>. </p>
								<p>The first volume contains the Pentateuch, Five Scrolls and Hafṭarot.</p>
								<p>The book of Ecclesiastes lacks chapters 9:10-12:14.</p>
								<p>At the end of the Hafṭarot, folios 296v-297r, there is Hosea 14:2-Joel 2:27, in a different hand. </p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="border">
								<locus n="2v"/>The Ten Commandments table in a colour-decorated panel - later addition.</decoNote>
						</msItem>
